{{Dialogue|Tainer|On the datapad, it's CCC-39.|Zekk|I'm telling you, the signs read WEDGE ANTILLES BOULEVARD.|Solo|Be quiet. It's got to be the same route. Cities rename their streets all the time.|attr=[[Doran Sarkin-Tainer]], [[Zekk]], and [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] argue while crossing Wedge Antilles Boulevard|src=<ref name="Betrayal" />}}
'''Wedge Antilles Boulevard''' was a street in [[Coronet City/Legends|Coronet City]], the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]]. It was once known as '''CCC-39''', but had been renamed<ref name="Betrayal" /> by [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]]<ref name="Date" /> in honor of [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], one of the most well-known [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] heroes at the [[Time/Legends|time]], although some maps still displayed the former name. Wedge Antilles Boulevard crossed under the wider, elevated [[Five Brothers Avenue]], which had much more traffic than the boulevard. A [[Team Purella|team]] of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] rode a [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]] across Wedge Antilles Boulevard in 40 ABY after unsuccessfully [[Operation Roundabout|attempting]] to arrest [[Five World Prime Minister]] [[Aidel Saxan]].<ref name="Betrayal" />

==Behind the scenes==
Wedge Antilles Boulevard was created by [[Aaron Allston]] for his [[2006]] novel ''[[Legacy of the Force: Betrayal]]'', the first volume in the ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' series.<ref name="Betrayal" />

